   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON FIVE THE PRACTICE OF</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE LORD'S TABLE MEETING 2 Scripture Reading: Matt 26:30; Heb 2:12; Eph 2:18; John 4:23-24 OUTLINE Worshipping the Father: After eating the bread and drinking the cup Matt 26:26-30.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>By praising Matt 26:30: Christ, the Firstborn of God, taking the lead among His brothers Heb 2:12.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>We, the many sons of God, following Christ in praising the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Addressing praise to the Father: Through the Son.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In the Spirit Eph 2:18.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Calling hymns: According to the Father's being.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>According to the Father's attributes.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>By presenting Christ to God the Father: As the peace offering Lev 3.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Enjoying Him before God the Father Lev 7:14-21, 28-34: As life supply vv.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>14-16.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>As love in resurrection vv.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>29-31.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>As power in ascension vv.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>32-34.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In cleanness vv.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>17-21.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Focus: The worshipping of the Father should be with the Son and in the Spirit John 4:23-24 .</S>
